  <summary date="2006-03-01T16:14:29Z" status="Introduced in House">Civil Rights Act of 1964 Commemorative Coin Act - Requires the Secretary of the Treasury to mint and issue, during 2014, no more than 350,000 one-dollar coins designed to be emblematic of the enactment of the Civil Rights Act of 1964 and its contribution to civil rights in America.

 Requires sales to include a $10 surcharge per coin, which shall be paid to the United Negro College Fund.</summary>
